msgstr "WINE 概述和概念"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:96
msgid ""
"WINE is a complex system, so before running it on a FreeBSD system it is worth gaining an understanding of what it "
"is and how it works."
msgstr "WINE 是一个复杂的系统，因此在 FreeBSD 系统上运行它之前，值得了解一下它是什么以及它是如何工作的。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is WINE?"
msgstr "什么是 WINE ？"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:102
msgid ""
"As mentioned in the <<wine-synopsis,Synopsis>> for this chapter, WINE is a compatibility layer that allows "
"Windows(R) applications to run on other operating systems.  In theory, it means these programs should run on "
"systems like FreeBSD, macOS, and Android."
msgstr ""
"正如本章简介中提到的，WINE 是一个兼容层，允许 Windows(R) 应用程序在其他操作系统上运行。在理论上，这意味着这些程序应"
"该在 FreeBSD 、 macOS 和 Android 等系统上运行。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:104
msgid "When WINE runs a Windows(R) executable, two things occur:"
msgstr "当 WINE 运行一个 Windows(R) 可执行文件时，会发生两件事："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:106
msgid ""
"Firstly, WINE implements an environment that mimics that of various versions of Windows(R). For example, if an "
"application requests access to a resource such as RAM, WINE has a memory interface that looks and acts (as far as "
"the application is concerned) like Windows(R)."
msgstr ""
"首先，WINE 实现了一个模仿各种版本的 Windows(R) 的环境。例如，如果一个应用程序要求访问一个资源，如 RAM ，WINE 有一个"
"内存接口，看起来和行动（就应用程序而言）都像 Windows(R) 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:107
msgid ""
"Then, once that application makes use of that interface, WINE takes the incoming request for space in memory and "
"translates it to something compatible with the host system. In the same way when the application retrieves that "
"data, WINE facilitates fetching it from the host system and passing it back to the Windows(R) application."
msgstr ""
"然后，假设该应用程序使用该接口，WINE 就会接收到对内存空间的传入请求，并将其转化为与主机系统兼容的东西。以同样的方"
"式，当应用程序检索该数据时，WINE 帮助从主机系统中获取该数据并将其传回给 Windows(R) 应用程序。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:109
#, no-wrap
msgid "WINE and the FreeBSD System"
msgstr "WINE 和 FreeBSD 系统"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:112
msgid "Installing WINE on a FreeBSD system will entail a few different components:"
msgstr "在 FreeBSD 系统上安装 WINE 将需要一些不同的组件："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:114
msgid ""
"FreeBSD applications for tasks such as running the Windows(R) executables, configuring the WINE sub-system, or "
"compiling programs with WINE support."
msgstr "用于运行 Windows(R) 可执行文件、配置 WINE 子系统或编译支持 WINE 的程序等任务的 FreeBSD 应用程序。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:115
msgid ""
"A large number of libraries that implement the core functions of Windows(R) (for example [.filename]#/lib/wine/api-"
"ms-core-memory-l1-1-1.dll.so#, which is part of the aforementioned memory interface)."
msgstr ""
"大量实现 Windows(R) 核心功能的库（例如 [.filename]#/lib/wine/api-ms-core-memory-l1-1-1.dll.so# ，它是上述内存接口的"
"一部分）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:116
msgid ""
"A number of Windows(R) executables, which are (or mimic) common utilities (such as [.filename]#/lib/wine/notepad."
"exe.so#, which provides the standard Windows(R) text editor)."
msgstr ""
"一些 Windows® 可执行文件，它们是（或模仿）常见的实用程序（例如 [.filename]#/lib/wine/notepad.exe.so# ，它提供标准"
"的 Windows(R) 文本编辑器）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:117
msgid ""
"Additional Windows(R) assets, in particular fonts (like the Tahoma font, which is stored in [.filename]#share/wine/"
"fonts/tahoma.ttf# in the install root)."
msgstr ""
"额外的 Windows(R) 组件，特别是字体（如 Tahoma 字体，它存储在安装根目录的 [.filename]#share/wine/fonts/tahoma.ttf# "
"中）。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Graphical Versus Text Mode/Terminal Programs in WINE"
msgstr "WINE 中图形与文本模式/终端程序的对比"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:124
msgid ""
"As an operating system where terminal utilities are \"first-class citizens,\" it is natural to assume that WINE "
"will contain extensive support for text-mode program.  However, the majority of applications for Windows(R), "
"especially the most popular ones, are designed with a graphical user interface (GUI) in mind.  Therefore, WINE's "
"utilities are designed by default to launch graphical programs."
msgstr ""
"作为一个终端工具是“头等公民”的操作系统，我们很自然地认为 WINE 将包含对文本模式程序的广泛支持。然而，大多数 "
"Windows(R) 的应用程序，特别是最流行的，都是以图形用户界面（GUI）为设计理念的。因此，WINE 的实用程序被默认设计为启动"
"图形程序。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:126
msgid "However, there are three methods available to run these so-called Console User Interface (CUI) programs:"
msgstr "然而，有三种方法可以运行这些所谓的控制台用户接口（CUI）程序："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:128
msgid "The _Bare Streams_ approach will display the output directly to standard output."
msgstr "_裸流_ 方法将直接显示输出到标准输出。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:129
msgid ""
"The _wineconsole_ utility can be used with either the _user_ or _curses_ backed to utilize some of the "
"enhancements the WINE system provides for CUI applications."
msgstr "_wineconsole_ 工具可以与 _用户_ 或 _curses_ 一起使用，以利用 WINE 系统为 CUI 程序提供的一些增强功能。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:131
msgid ""
"These approaches are described in greater detail on the https://wiki.winehq.org/Wine_User"
"%27s_Guide#Text_mode_programs_.28CUI:_Console_User_Interface.29[WINE Wiki]."
msgstr ""
"这些方法在 https://wiki.winehq.org/Wine_User%27s_Guide#Text_mode_programs_.28CUI:_Console_User_Interface.29[WINE "
"Wiki] 上有更详细的描述。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:133
#, no-wrap
msgid "WINE Derivative Projects"
msgstr "WINE 衍生项目"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:136
msgid ""
"WINE itself is a mature open source project, so it is little surprise it is used as the foundation of more complex "
"solutions."
msgstr "WINE 本身是一个成熟的开源项目，所以它被用作更复杂的解决方案的基础也就不足为奇。"

