#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternatives to WINE"
msgstr "WINE 的替代方案"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:173
msgid "For FreeBSD users, some alternatives to using WINE are as follows:"
msgstr "对于 FreeBSD 用户，使用 WINE 的一些替代方案如下："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:175
msgid ""
"Dual-Booting: A straightforward option is to run desired Windows(R) applications natively on that OS. This of "
"course means existing FreeBSD in order to boot Windows(R), so this method is not feasible if access to programs in "
"both systems is required simultaneously."
msgstr ""
"双启动。一个直接的选择是在该操作系统上原生地运行所需的 Windows(R) 应用程序。这当然意味着要在现有的 FreeBSD 上启动 "
"Windows(R) ，所以如果需要同时访问两个系统的程序，这个方法是不可行的。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:176
msgid ""
"Virtual Machines: Virtual Machines (VMs), as mentioned earlier in this chapter, are software processes that "
"emulate full sets of hardware, on which additional operating systems (including Windows(R)) can be installed and "
"run. Modern tools make VMs easy to create and manage, but this method comes at a cost. A good portion of the host "
"systems resources must be allocated to each VM, and those resources cannot be reclaimed by the host as long as the "
"VM is running. A few examples of VM managers include the open source solutions qemu, bhyve, and VirtualBox. See "
"the chapter on <<virtualization,Virtualization>> for more detail."
msgstr ""
"虚拟机。虚拟机（VM），正如本章前面提到的，是模拟全套硬件的软件进程，在其上可以安装和运行其他操作系统（包括 "
"Windows(R) ）。现代工具使虚拟机易于创建和管理，但这种方法是有代价的。主机系统的很大一部分资源必须分配给每个虚拟机，"
"而且只要虚拟机在运行，主机就不能回收这些资源。虚拟机管理器的几个例子包括开源解决方案 qemu 、 bhyve 和 VirtualBox 。"
"更多细节请参见虚拟化一章。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:177
msgid ""
"Remote Access: Like many other UNIX(R)-like systems, FreeBSD can run a variety of applications enabling users to "
"remotely access Windows(R) computers and use their programs or data. In addtion to clients such as xrdp that "
"connect to the standard Windows(R) Remote Desktop Protocol, other open source standards such as vnc can also be "
"used (provided a compatible server is present on the other side)."
msgstr ""
"远程访问。像许多其他类似 UNIX(R) 的系统一样，FreeBSD 可以运行各种应用程序，使用户能够远程访问 Windows(R) 计算机并使"
"用他们的程序或数据。除了像 xrdp 这样连接到标准的 Windows(R) 远程桌面协议的客户端之外，还可以使用其他开源标准，如 "
"vnc （只要另一端有兼容的服务器）。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:179
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing WINE on FreeBSD"
msgstr "在 FreeBSD 上安装 WINE"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:182
msgid "WINE can be installed via the pkg tool, or by compiling the port(s)."
msgstr "可以通过 pkg 工具安装 WINE，也可以通过 ports 编译安装 WINE。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:184
#, no-wrap
msgid "WINE Prerequistes"
msgstr "WINE 的安装需求"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:187
msgid "Before installing WINE itself, it is useful to have the following pre-requisites installed."
msgstr "在安装 WINE 本身之前，安装以下的先决软件是很有用的："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:189
msgid "A GUI"
msgstr "一个图形用户界面"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:193
msgid ""
"Most Windows(R) programs are expecting to have a graphical user interface available.  If WINE is installed without "
"one present, its dependencies will include the Wayland compositor, and so a GUI will be installed along with "
"WINE.  But it is useful to have the GUI of choice installed, configured, and working correctly before installing "
"WINE."
msgstr ""
"大多数 Windows(R) 程序都希望有一个图形化的用户界面。如果 WINE在安装时没有图形用户界面，它的依赖关系将包括 Wayland "
"合成器，因此图形用户界面将与 WINE 一起安装。但在安装 WINE 之前，安装、配置并正确运行所选择的 GUI 是很有用的。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:195
msgid "wine-gecko"
msgstr "wine-gecko"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:201
msgid ""
"The Windows(R) operating system has for some time had a default web browser pre-installed: Internet Explorer.  As "
"a result, some applications work under the assumption that there will always be something capable of displaying "
"web pages.  In order to provide this functionality, the WINE layer includes a web browser component using the "
"Mozilla project's Gecko engine.  When WINE is first launched it will offer to download and install this, and there "
"are reasons users might want it do so (these will be covered in a later chapter).  But they can also install it "
"prior to installing WINE, or alongside the install of WINE proper."
msgstr ""
"一段时间以来，Windows(R) 操作系统已经预装了一个默认的网络浏览器。Internet Explorer 。因此，一些应用程序在工作时假定"
"总是有能够显示网页的东西。为了提供这种功能，WINE 层包括一个使用Mozilla 项目的 Gecko 引擎的网络浏览器组件。当 WINE "
"首次启动时，它将提供下载和安装，而且用户可能希望它这样做（这些将在后面的章节中介绍）。但他们也可以在安装 WINE 之前"
"安装它，或者在安装 WINE 的同时安装。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:203
msgid "Install this package with the following:"
msgstr "用下面的方法安装这个包："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:207
#, no-wrap
msgid "# pkg install wine-gecko\n"
msgstr "# pkg install wine-gecko\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:210
msgid "Alternately, compile the port with the following:"
msgstr "或者，用下面的方法 ports 编译："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:215
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulator/wine-gecko\n"
"# make install\n"
msgstr ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulator/wine-gecko\n"
"# make install\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:218
msgid "wine-mono"
msgstr "wine-mono"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:221
msgid ""
"This port installs the MONO framework, an open source implementation of Microsoft's .NET.  Including this with the "
"WINE installation will make it that much more likely that any applications written in .NET will install and run on "
"the system."
msgstr ""
"这个 port 安装了 MONO 框架，一个微软 .NET 的开源实现。在 WINE的安装中包括这个，将使任何用 .NET 编写的应用程序更有可"
"能在系统上安装和运行。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:223
msgid "To install the package:"
msgstr "要安装该软件包："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:227
#, no-wrap
msgid "# pkg install wine-mono\n"
msgstr "# pkg install wine-mono\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:230
msgid "To compile from the ports collection:"
msgstr "从 ports 集合中进行编译："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulator/wine-mono\n"
"# make install\n"
msgstr ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulator/wine-mono\n"
"# make install\n"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:238
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing WINE via FreeBSD Package Repositories"
msgstr "通过 FreeBSD 软件包库安装 WINE"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:241
msgid "With the pre-requisites in place, install WINE via package with the following command:"
msgstr "有了这些先决条件，用下面的命令通过软件包来安装 WINE："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:245
#, no-wrap
msgid "# pkg install wine\n"
msgstr "# pkg install wine\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:248
msgid "Alternately compile the WINE sub-system from source with the following:"
msgstr "或者用下面的命令从源代码编译 WINE 子系统："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:253
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulator/wine\n"
"# make install\n"
msgstr ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulator/wine\n"
"# make install\n"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:256
#, no-wrap
msgid "Concerns of 32- Versus 64-Bit in WINE Installations"
msgstr "WINE 安装中的 32 位与 64 位的关注点"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:261
msgid ""
"Like most software, Windows(R) applications made the upgrade from the older 32-bit architecture to 64 bits.  And "
"most recent software is written for 64-bit operating systems, although modern OSes can sometimes continue to run "
"older 32-bit programs as well.  FreeBSD is no different, having had support for 64-bit since the 5.x series."
msgstr ""
"像大多数软件一样，Windows(R) 应用程序从旧的 32 位架构升级到 64 位。而且大多数最新的软件都是为 64 位操作系统编写的，"
"尽管现代操作系统有时也可以继续运行旧的 32 位程序。FreeBSD 也不例外，从 5.x 系列开始就有对 64 位的支持。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:264
msgid ""
"However, using old software no longer supported by default is a common use for emulators, and users commonly turn "
"to WINE to play games and use other programs that do not run properly on modern hardware.  Fortunately, FreeBSD "
"can support all three scenarios:"
msgstr ""
"然而，使用默认情况下不再支持的旧软件是模拟器的一个常见用途，用户通常转向 WINE 来玩游戏和使用其他在现代硬件上不能正"
"常运行的程序。幸运的是，FreeBSD 可以支持所有这三种情况。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:266
msgid ""
"On modern, 64-bit machine and want to run 64-bit Windows(R) software, simply install the ports mentioned in the "
"above sections. The ports system will automatically install the 64-bit version."
msgstr ""
"在现代的 64 位机器上，想要运行 64 位的 Windows(R) 软件，只需安装上面几节中提到的 ports 。ports 系统会自动安装 64 位"
"版本。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:267
msgid ""
"Alternately, users might have an older 32-bit machine that they do not want to run with its original, now non-"
"supported software. They can install the 32-bit (i386) version of FreeBSD, then install the ports in the above "
"sections. Again, on a 32-bit machine the ports system will install the corresponding 32-bit version of WINE by "
"default."
msgstr ""
"另外，用户可能有一台旧的 32 位机器，他们不想用原来的、现在不支持的软件运行。他们可以安装 32-bit (i386) 版本的 "
"FreeBSD，然后再安装上面几节中的 ports。同样，在 32 位机器上，ports 系统会默认安装相应的 32 位版本的 WINE 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:270
msgid ""
"However, given a 64-bit version of FreeBSD and need to run *32-bit* Windows(R) applications, installing a "
"different port is required to enable 32-bit compatibility.  To install the pre-compiled package, use the following:"
msgstr ""
"然而，如果是 64 位版本的 FreeBSD ，并需要运行 32 位的 Windows(R) 应用程序，则需要安装不同的 ports 以实现 32 位的兼"
"容性。要安装预先编译好的软件包，请使用以下方法："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "# pkg install i386-wine\n"
msgstr "# pkg install i386-wine\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:277
msgid "Or compile the port with the following:"
msgstr "或者用下面的方法 ports 编译："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:282
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulator/i386-wine\n"
"# make install\n"
msgstr ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulator/i386-wine\n"
"# make install\n"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:285
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running a First WINE Program on FreeBSD"
msgstr "在 FreeBSD 上运行第一个 WINE 程序"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:289
msgid ""
"Now that WINE is installed, the next step is to try it out by running a simple program.  An easy way to do this is "
"to download a self-contained application, i.e., one can simply unpack and run without any complex installation "
"process."
msgstr ""
"现在 WINE 已经安装好了，下一步是通过运行一个简单的程序来试试。简单的方法是下载一个独立的应用程序，也就是说，可以简"
"单地解压和运行程序而不需要任何复杂的安装过程。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:291
msgid ""
"So-called \"portable\" versions of applications are good choices for this test, as are programs that run with only "
"a single executable file."
msgstr "所谓的“可移植”版本的应用程序是这种测试的好选择，只用一个可执行文件运行的程序也是如此。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:293
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running a Program from the Command Line"
msgstr "从命令行运行一个程序"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:297
msgid ""
"There are two different methods to launch a Windows program from the terminal.  The first, and most "
"straightforward is to navigate to the directory containing the program's executable ([.filename]#.EXE#) and issue "
"the following:"
msgstr ""
"有两种不同的方法可以从终端启动一个 Windows 程序。第一种，也是最直接的一种，是导航到包含程序可执行文件"
"（[.filename]#.EXE#）的目录，然后执行以下命令："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:301
#, no-wrap
msgid "% wine program.exe\n"
msgstr "% wine program.exe\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:304
msgid "For applications that take command-line arguments, add them after the executable as usual:"
msgstr "对于需要命令行参数的应用程序，像往常一样在可执行文件后添加参数："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "% wine program2.exe -file file.txt\n"
msgstr "% wine program2.exe -file file.txt\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:311
msgid "Alternately, supply the full path to the executable to use it in a script, for example:"
msgstr "另外，提供可执行文件的完整路径，以便在脚本中使用它，例如："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "% wine /home/user/bin/program.exe\n"
msgstr "% wine /home/user/bin/program.exe\n"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:318
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running a Program from a GUI"
msgstr "使用 GUI 运行一个程序"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:322
msgid ""
"After installation graphical shells should be updated with new associations for Windows executable ([.filename]#."
"EXE#) files.  It will now be possible to browse the system using a file manager, and launch the Windows "
"application in the same way as other files and programs (either a single- or double-click, depending on the "
"desktop's settings)."
msgstr ""
"安装后，图形外壳应更新为与 Windows 可执行文件（[.filename]#.EXE#）有关的新关联。现在可以使用文件管理器浏览系统，并"
"以与其他文件和程序相同的方式启动 Windows 应用程序（单击或双击，取决于桌面的设置）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:325
msgid ""
"On most desktops, check to make sure this association is correct by right-clicking on the file, and looking for an "
"entry in the context menu to open the file.  One of the options (hopefully the default one) will be with the *Wine "
"Windows Program Loader*, as shown in the below screenshot:"
msgstr ""
"在大多数桌面上，通过右键点击文件，并在上下文菜单中寻找打开文件的条目，来检查确保这种关联是正确的。其中一个选项（希"
"望是默认选项）将是与 *Wine Windows 程序加载器*，如下面的截图所示："

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:326
#, no-wrap
msgid "wine-run-np++-1.png"
msgstr "wine-run-np++-1.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:329
msgid ""
"In the event the program does not run as expected, try launching it from the command line and review any messages "
"displayed in the terminal to troubleshoot."
msgstr "如果程序不能按预期运行，请尝试从命令行启动它，并查看终端显示的任何信息以排除故障。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:331
msgid ""
"In the event WINE is not the default application for [.filename]#.EXE# files after install, check the MIME "
"associate for this extension in the current desktop environment, graphical shell, or file manager."
msgstr ""
"如果 WINE 在安装后不是 [.filename]#.EXE# 文件的默认应用程序，请检查当前桌面环境、图形化壳或文件管理器中该扩展名的 "
"MIME 关联。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:333
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring WINE Installation"
msgstr "配置 WINE 安装"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:337
msgid ""
"With an understanding of what WINE is and how it works at a high level, the next step to effectively using it on "
"FreeBSD is becoming familiar with its configuration.  The following sections will describe the key concept of the "
"_WINE prefix_, and illustrate how it is used to control the behavior of applications run through WINE."
msgstr ""
"在了解了什么是 WINE 以及它如何在高层次上工作之后，在 FreeBSD上有效使用它的下一步就是熟悉它的配置。下面几节将描述 "
"_WINE Prefix_ 的关键概念，并说明如何用它来控制通过 WINE 运行的应用程序的行为。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:339
#, no-wrap
msgid "WINE Prefixes"
msgstr "WINE Prefixes"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:344
msgid ""
"A WINE _prefix_ is a directory, usually located beneath the default location of [.filename]#$HOME/.wine# though it "
"can be located elsewhere.  The prefix is a set of configurations and support files used by the wine to configure "
"and run the Windows(R) environment a given application needs.  By default, a brand new WINE installation will "
"create the following structure when first launched by a user:"
msgstr ""
"WINE _Prefix_ 是一个目录，通常位于 [.filename]#$HOME/.wine# 的默认位置之下，尽管它可以位于其他地方。WINE Prefix 是"
"一组配置和支持文件，由 wine 用来配置和运行特定应用程序所需的 Windows(R) 环境。默认情况下，一个全新的WINE安装在用户"
"首次启动时将创建以下结构。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:346
msgid ""
"[.filename]#.update-timestamp#: contains the last modified date of [.filename]#file /usr/share/wine/wine.inf#. It "
"is used by WINE to determine if a prefix is out of date, and automatically update it if needed."
msgstr ""
"[.filename]#.update-timestamp# ：包含文件 [.filename]#file /usr/share/wine/wine.inf# 的最后修改日期。它被 WINE 用来"
"判断一个 WINE Prefix 是否过时，并在需要时自动更新它。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:347
msgid ""
"[.filename]#dosdevices/#: contains information on mappings of Windows(R) resources to resources on the host "
"FreeBSD system. For example, after a new WINE installation, this should contain at least two entries which enable "
"access to the FreeBSD filesystem using Windows(R)-style drive letters:"
msgstr ""
"[.filename]#dosdevices/# : 包含 Windows(R) 资源与主机FreeBSD系统上的资源的映射信息。例如，在新的WINE安装之后，这里"
"应该至少包含两个条目，可以使用 Windows(R) 风格的驱动器字母来访问 FreeBSD 的文件系统。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:349
msgid "[.filename]#c:@#: A link to [.filename]#drive_c# described below."
msgstr "[.filename]#c:@# : 与下面描述的 [.filename]#drive_c# 的链接。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:350
msgid "[.filename]#z:@#: A link to the root directory of the system."
msgstr "[.filename]#z:@# : 到系统根目录的链接。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:352
msgid ""
"[.filename]#drive_c/#: emulates the main (i.e., [.filename]#C:#) drive of a Windows(R) system. It contains a "
"directory structure and associated files mirroring that of standard Windows(R) systems. A fresh WINE prefix will "
"contain Windows(R) 10 directories such as _Users_ and _Windows_ that holds the OS itself. Furthermore, "
"applications installed within a prefix will be located in either _Program Files_ or _Program Files (x86)_, "
"depending on their architecture."
msgstr ""
"[.filename]#drive_c/# : 模拟 Windows(R) 系统的主驱动器（即 [.filename]#C:# ）。它包含一个目录结构和相关文件，与标准"
"的 Windows(R) 系统一样。一个新的 WINE Prefixes 将包含 Windows(R) 10 目录，如 _Users_ 和 _Windows_ ，其中包含操作系"
"统本身。此外，安装在 WINE Prefixes 中的应用程序将位于 _Program Files_ 或 _Program Files (x86)_ 中，这取决于其架构。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:353
msgid ""
"[.filename]#system.reg#: This Registry file contains information on the Windows(R) installation, which in the case "
"of WINE is the environment in [.filename]#drive_c#."
msgstr ""
"[.filename]#system.reg#：这个注册表文件包含了 Windows(R) 安装的信息，在 WINE 的情况下，它是 [.filename]#drive_c# 中"
"的环境。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:354
msgid ""
"[.filename]#user.reg#: This Registry file contains the current user's personal configurations, made either by "
"varous software or through the use of the Registry Editor."
msgstr "[.filename]#user.reg# : 这个注册表文件包含了当前用户的个人配置，由各种软件或通过使用注册表编辑器来完成。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:355
msgid "[.filename]#userdef.reg#: This Registry file is a default set of configurations for newly-created users."
msgstr "[.filename]#userdef.reg# : 这个注册表文件是新创建的用户的默认配置集。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:357
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating and Using WINE Prefixes"
msgstr "创建和使用 WINE Prefixes"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:361
msgid ""
"While WINE will create a default prefix in the user's [.filename]#$HOME/.wine/#, it is possible to set up multiple "
"prefixes.  There are a few reasons to do this:"
msgstr ""
"虽然 WINE 会在用户的 [.filename]#$HOME/.wine/# 中创建一个默认 WINE Prefixes ，但也可以设置多个 WINE Prefixes。这样"
"做有几个原因："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:363
msgid ""
"The most common reason is to emulate different versions of Windows(R), according to the compatibility needs of the "
"software in question."
msgstr "最常见的原因是根据有关软件的兼容性需要，模拟不同版本的 Windows(R) 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:364
msgid ""
"In addition, it is common to encounter software that does not work correctly in the default environment, and "
"requires special configuration. it is useful to isolate these in their own, custom prefixes, so the changes do not "
"impact other applications."
msgstr ""
"此外，经常会遇到一些在默认环境下不能正常工作的软件，需要进行特殊的配置。将这些软件隔离在自己的自定义 WINE Prefixes "
"中是很有用的，这样的改变不会影响其他应用程序。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:365
msgid ""
"Similarly, copying the default or \"main\" prefix into a separate \"testing\" one in order to evaluate an "
"application's compatibility can reduce the chance of corruption."
msgstr ""
"同样，为了评估一个应用程序的兼容性，将默认或 \" main \" Prefixes 复制到一个单独的 \" testing \" Prefixes 中，可以减"
"少出错的可能性。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:367
msgid "Creating a prefix from the terminal requires the following command:"
msgstr "从终端创建一个 WINE Prefixes 需要使用以下命令："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:371
#, no-wrap
msgid "% WINEPREFIX=\"/home/username/.wine-new\" winecfg\n"
msgstr "% WINEPREFIX=\"/home/username/.wine-new\" winecfg\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:375
msgid ""
"This will run the winecfg program, which can be used to configure wine prefixes (more on this in a later "
"section).  But by providing a directory path value for the `WINEPREFIX` environment variable, a new prefix is "
"created at that location if one does not already exist."
msgstr ""
"这将运行 winecfg 程序，该程序可用于配置 WINE Prefixes（在后面的章节中会有更多介绍）。但通过为 `WINEPREFIX` 环境变量"
"提供一个目录路径值，如果一个 WINE Prefixes 还不存在，就会在该位置创建一个新的 WINE Prefixes："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:377
msgid ""
"Supplying the same variable to the wine program will similarly cause the selected program to be run with the "
"specified prefix:"
msgstr "向 wine 程序提供同样的变量，同样会导致所选程序以指定的 WINE Prefixes 运行："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:381
#, no-wrap
msgid "% WINEPREFIX=\"/home/username/.wine-new\" wine program.exe\n"
msgstr "% WINEPREFIX=\"/home/username/.wine-new\" wine program.exe\n"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:384
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring WINE Prefixes with winecfg"
msgstr "用 winecfg 配置 WINE Prefixes"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:389
msgid ""
"As described above WINE includes a tool called winecfg to configure prefixes from within a GUI.  It contains a "
"variety of functions, which are detailed in the sections below.  When winecfg is run from within a prefix, or "
"provided the location of a prefix within the `WINEPREFIX` variable, it enables the configuration of the selected "
"prefix as described in the below sections."
msgstr ""
"如上所述，WINE包括一个名为 winecfg 的工具，可以在图形用户界面中配置 WINE Prefixes 。它包含各种功能，在下面的章节中"
"会详细介绍。当 winecfg 从一个 WINE Prefixes 中运行时，或者在 `WINEPREFIX` 变量中提供一个 WINE Prefixes 的位置时，它"
"就可以对所选的 Prefixes 进行配置，如以下各节所述。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:392
msgid ""
"Selections made on the _Applications_ tab will affect the scope of changes made in the _Libraries_ and _Graphics_ "
"tabs, which will be limited to the application selected.  See the section on https://wiki.winehq.org/Wine_User"
"%27s_Guide#Using_Winecfg[Using Winecfg] in the WINE Wiki for more details."
msgstr ""
"在 \"应用程序 \"选项卡上进行的选择将影响在 _Libraries_ 和 _Graphics_ 选项卡上的更改范围，这些更改将被限制在所选的应"
"用程序中。更多细节请参见 https://wiki.winehq.org/Wine_User%27s_Guide#Using_Winecfg[Using Winecfg] 中关于使用 "
"Winecfg 的部分。"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:394
#, no-wrap
msgid "Applications"
msgstr "应用程序"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:396
#, no-wrap
msgid "wine-config-1.png"
msgstr "wine-config-1.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:401
msgid ""
"The _Applications_ contains controls enabling the association of programs with a particular version of "
"Windows(R).  On first start-up the _Application settings_ section will contain a single entry: _Default "
"Settings_.  This corresponds to all the default configurations of the prefix, which (as the disabled _Remove "
"application_ button implies) cannot be deleted."
msgstr ""
"_Applications_ 包含了使程序与特定版本的 Windows(R) 相关联的控制。第一次启动时，_应用程序设置_ 部分将包含一个条目： "
"_默认设置_ 。这相当于 WINE Prefixes 的所有默认配置，（正如禁用的 _删除应用程序_ 按钮所暗示的）不能被删除。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:403
msgid "But additional applications can be added with the following process:"
msgstr "但可以通过以下过程添加额外的应用程序："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:405
msgid "Click the _Add application_ button."
msgstr "单击 _Add application_ 按钮。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:406
msgid "Use the provided dialog to select the desired program's executable."
msgstr "使用提供的对话框选择所需的程序的可执行文件。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:407
msgid "Select the version of Windows(R) to be used with the selected program."
msgstr "选择要与所选程序一起使用的 Windows(R) 版本。"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:409
#, no-wrap
msgid "Libraries"
msgstr "库"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:411
#, no-wrap
msgid "wine-config-2.png"
msgstr "wine-config-2.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:416
msgid ""
"WINE provides a set of open source library files as part of its distribution that provide the same functions as "
"their Windows(R) counterparts.  However, as noted earlier in this chapter, the WINE project is always trying to "
"keep pace with new updates to these libraries.  As a result, the versions that ship with WINE may be missing "
"functionality that the latest Windows(R) programs are expecting."
msgstr ""
"WINE 提供了一组开源的库文件作为其发行的一部分，这些库文件提供了与 Windows(R) 对应的相同功能。然而，正如本章前面所提"
"到的，WINE 项目一直在努力跟上这些库的新更新。因此，与 WINE 一起发行的版本可能缺少最新 Windows(R) 程序所期望的功能。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:418
msgid ""
"However, winecfg makes it possible specify overrides for the built-in libraries, particularly there is a version "
"of Windows(R) available on the same machine as the host FreeBSD installation. For each library to be overridden, "
"do the following:"
msgstr ""
"然而，winecfg 可以为内置的库指定重写，特别是在安装 FreeBSD 的同一台机器上有 Windows(R) 的版本。对于每一个要被覆盖的"
"库，请执行以下操作："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:420
msgid "Open the _New override for library_ drop-down and select the library to be replaced."
msgstr "打开 _New override for library_ 下拉菜单，选择要替换的库。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:421
msgid "Click the _Add_ button."
msgstr "点击 _Add_ 按钮。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:422
msgid ""
"The new override will appear in the _Existing overrides_ list, notice the _native, builtin_ designation in "
"parentheses."
msgstr "新的覆盖将出现在 _Existing overrides_ 列表中，注意括号中的 _native、builtin_ 指定。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:423
msgid "Click to select the library."
msgstr "点击选择该库。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:424
msgid "Click the _Edit_ button."
msgstr "点击 _Edit_ 按钮。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:425
msgid "Use the provided dialog to select a corresponding library to be used in place of the built-in one."
msgstr "使用提供的对话框选择一个相应的库来代替内置库。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:427
msgid ""
"Be sure to select a file that is truly the corresponding version of the built-in one, otherwise there may be "
"unexpected behavior."
msgstr "请确保选择一个真正与内置库对应的文件，否则可能会有意想不到的行为。"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:429
#, no-wrap
msgid "Graphics"
msgstr "图形"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:431
#, no-wrap
msgid "wine-config-3.png"
msgstr "wine-config-3.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:434
msgid ""
"The _Graphics_ tab provides some options to make the windows of programs run via WINE operate smoothly with FreeBSD"
msgstr "_图形_ 选项卡提供了一些选项，使通过 WINE 运行的程序的窗口能够在 FreeBSD 中顺利运行："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:436
msgid "Automatic mouse capture when windows are full-screen."
msgstr "当窗口为全屏时自动捕捉鼠标。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:437
msgid ""
"Allowing the FreeBSD window manager to decorate the windows, such as their title bars, for programs running via "
"WINE."
msgstr "允许 FreeBSD 的窗口管理器装饰窗口，例如通过 WINE 运行的程序的标题栏。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:438
msgid ""
"Allowing the window manager to control windows for programs running via WINE, such as running resizing functions "
"on them."
msgstr "允许窗口管理器为通过 WINE 运行的程序控制窗口，例如对它们运行调整大小的功能。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:439
msgid ""
"Create an emulated virtual desktop, within which all WINE programs will run. If this item is selected, the size of "
"the virtual desktop can be specified using the _Desktop size_ input boxes."
msgstr ""
"创建一个模拟的虚拟桌面，所有 WINE 程序将在其中运行。如果选择了这个项目，虚拟桌面的大小可以用 _桌面大小_ 输入框来指"
"定。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:440
msgid "Setting the screen resolution for programs running via WINE."
msgstr "为通过 WINE 运行的程序设置屏幕分辨率。"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:442
#, no-wrap
msgid "Desktop Integration"
msgstr "桌面集成"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:444
#, no-wrap
msgid "wine-config-4.png"
msgstr "wine-config-4.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:447
msgid "This tab allows configuration of the following items:"
msgstr "这个标签允许配置以下项目："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:449
msgid "The theme and related visual settings to be used for programs running via WINE."
msgstr "通过 WINE 运行的程序要使用的主题和相关的视觉设置。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:450
msgid ""
"Whether the WINE sub-system should manage MIME types (used to determine which application opens a particular file "
"type) internally."
msgstr "WINE 子系统是否应该在内部管理 MIME 类型（用于确定哪个应用程序打开特定的文件类型）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:451
msgid ""
"Mappings of directories in the host FreeBSD system to useful folders within the Windows(R) environment. To change "
"an existing association, select the desired item and click _Browse_, then use the provided dialog to select a "
"directory."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 主机系统中的目录与 Windows(R) 环境中的有用文件夹的映射。要改变现有的关联，选择所需的项目并点击浏览，然后使"
"用提供的对话框选择一个目录。"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:453
#, no-wrap
msgid "Drives"
msgstr "驱动器"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:455
#, no-wrap
msgid "wine-config-5.png"
msgstr "wine-config-5.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:460
msgid ""
"The _Drives_ tab allows linking of directories in the host FreeBSD system to drive letters in the Windows(R) "
"environment.  The default values in this tab should look familiar, as they're displaying the contents of [."
"filename]#dosdevices/# in the current WINE prefix.  Changes made via this dialog will reflect in [."
"filename]#dosdevices#, and properly-formatted links created in that directory will display in this tab."
msgstr ""
"_Drives_ 选项卡允许将主机 FreeBSD 系统中的目录与 Windows(R) 环境中的驱动器字母联系起来。这个选项卡中的默认值应该看"
"起来很熟悉，因为它们显示的是当前 WINE Prefixes 中 [.filename]#dosdevices/# 的内容。通过这个对话框所做的改变将反映"
"在 [.filename]#dosdevices# 中，在该目录中创建的正确格式的链接将显示在这个标签中。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:462
msgid "To create a new entry, such as for a CD-ROM (mounted at [.filename]#/mnt/cdrom#), take the following steps:"
msgstr "要创建一个新的条目，例如 CD-ROM（挂载在 [.filename]#/mnt/cdrom# ），采取以下步骤："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:464
msgid "Click the _Add _ button."
msgstr "点击 _Add_ 按钮。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:465
msgid "In the provided dialog, choose a free drive letter."
msgstr "在提供的对话框中，选择一个空闲的盘符。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:466
msgid "Click _OK_."
msgstr "点击 _OK_ 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:467
msgid ""
"Fill in the _Path_ input box by either typing the path to the resource, or click _Browse _ and use the provided "
"dialog to select it."
msgstr "在 _路径_ 输入框中输入资源的路径，或者点击 _Browse_ 并使用提供的对话框来选择它。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:470
msgid ""
"By default WINE will autodetect the type of resource linked, but this can be manually overridden.  See https://"
"wiki.winehq.org/Wine_User%27s_Guide#Drive_Settings[the section in the WINE Wiki] for more detail on advanced "
"options."
msgstr ""
"默认情况下，WINE 会自动检测所链接的资源类型，但这可以被手动覆盖。关于高级选项的更多细节，请参见 "
"https://wiki.winehq.org/Wine_User%27s_Guide#Drive_Settings[the section in the WINE Wiki] 中的章节。"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:472
#, no-wrap
msgid "Audio"
msgstr "音频"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:474
#, no-wrap
msgid "wine-config-6.png"
msgstr "wine-config-6.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:477
msgid ""
"This tab contains some configurable options for routing sound from Windows(R) programs to the native FreeBSD sound "
"system, including:"
msgstr "这个选项卡包含了一些可配置的选项，用于将 Windows(R) 程序的声音路由到原生的 FreeBSD 声音系统，包括："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:479
msgid "Driver selection"
msgstr "驱动程序选择"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:480
msgid "Default device selection"
msgstr "默认设备选择"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:481
msgid "Sound test"
msgstr "声音测试"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:483
#, no-wrap
msgid "About"
msgstr "关于"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:485
#, no-wrap
msgid "wine-config-7.png"
msgstr "wine-config-7.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:489
msgid ""
"The final tab contains information on the WINE project, including a link to the website.  It also allows entry of "
"(entirely optional) user information, although this is not sent anywhere as it is in other operating systems."
msgstr ""
"最后一个标签包含了关于 WINE 项目的信息，包括一个网站的链接。它还允许输入（完全可选的）用户信息，尽管这些信息不会像"
"其他操作系统那样被发送到任何地方。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:491
#, no-wrap
msgid "WINE Management GUIs"
msgstr "WINE 图形管理用户界面"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:496
msgid ""
"While the base install of WINE comes with a GUI configuration tool in winecfg, it is main purpose is just that: "
"strictly configuring an existing WINE prefix.  There are, however, more advanced applications that will assist in "
"the initial installation of applications as well as optimizing their WINE environments.  The below sections "
"include a selection of the most popular."
msgstr ""
"虽然 WINE 的基本安装包含一个 winecfg 的 GUI 配置工具，但它的主要目的只是：严格配置现有的 WINE Prefixes 。然而，还有"
"一些更高级的应用程序，它们将协助应用程序的初始安装，以及优化它们的 WINE 环境。下面的章节包括了一些最流行的选择。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:498
#, no-wrap
msgid "Winetricks"
msgstr "Winetricks"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:503
msgid ""
"winetricks is a cross-platform, general purpose helper program for WINE.  It is not developed by the WINE project "
"proper, but rather maintained on https://github.com/Winetricks/winetricks[Github] by a group of contributors.  It "
"contains some automated \"recipes\" for getting common applications to work on WINE, both by optimizing the "
"settings as well as acquiring some DLL libraries automatically."
msgstr ""
"winetricks 是一个跨平台的、通用的 WINE 辅助程序。它不是由 WINE 项目本身开发的，而是由一群贡献者在"
" https://github.com/Winetricks/winetricks[Github] 上维护。它包含了一些自动的“配方”，通过优化设置以及自动获取一些 DLL 库，使普通应用"
"程序在 WINE 上运行。"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:505
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing winetricks"
msgstr "安装 winetricks"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:508
msgid ""
"To install winetricks on a FreeBSD using binary packages, use the following commands (note winetricks requires "
"either the i386-wine or i386-wine-devel package, and is therefore not installed automatically with other "
"dependencies):"
msgstr ""
"要在使用二进制包的 FreeBSD 上安装 winetricks，请使用以下命令（注意 winetricks 需要 i386-wine 或 i386-wine-devel "
"包，因此不会与其他依赖项一起自动安装）："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:512
#, no-wrap
msgid "# pkg install i386-wine winetricks\n"
msgstr "# pkg install i386-wine winetricks\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:515
msgid "To compile it from source, issue the following in the terminal:"
msgstr "要从源代码编译它，请在终端发出以下命令："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:522
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulators/i386-wine\n"
"# make install\n"
"# cd /usr/ports/emulators/winetricks\n"
"# make install\n"
msgstr ""
"# cd /usr/ports/emulators/i386-wine\n"
"# make install\n"
"# cd /usr/ports/emulators/winetricks\n"
"# make install\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:525
msgid ""
"If a manual installation is required, refer to the https://github.com/Winetricks/winetricks[Github] account for "
"instructions."
msgstr "如果需要手动安装，请参考 https://github.com/Winetricks/winetricks[Github] 账户的说明。"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:527
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using winetricks"
msgstr "使用 winetricks"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:530
msgid "Run winetricks with the following command:"
msgstr "用以下命令运行 winetricks："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:534
#, no-wrap
msgid "% winetricks\n"
msgstr "% winetricks\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:538
msgid ""
"Note: this should be in a 32-bit prefix to run winetricks.  Launching winetricks displays a window with a number "
"of choices, as follows:"
msgstr ""
